1. git init
initialize git, it creates a hidden lib ./git and the repository for project

2. git status
ask for git status

3. git add fileName/.(add all untrack files)
tell the git to track the file

4. git commit -m "(the changes you made)"
commit the tracked file

5. git log
show all previous commit history

6. git checkout commit_id
set HEAD to point back to the previous commit node

7. git revert --no-commit commit_id..HEAD
go back to the commit status where HEAD points

8. git push heroku master
after add and commit all files into git repository, push the master to heroku

9. heroku logs
check the error message sent back

10. heroku run _command
connect to heroku server and run the command in heroku command line
